### Step 2: Create a Service for Stripe

Create a service to handle Stripe operations. This service will include methods to create a customer and a subscription.

```typescript
import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';
import Stripe from 'stripe';

@Injectable()
export class StripeService {
  private stripe: Stripe;

  constructor() {
    this.stripe = new Stripe('your_stripe_secret_key', {
      apiVersion: '2022-11-15',
    });
  }

  async createCustomer(email: string, name: string): Promise<Stripe.Customer> {
    return await this.stripe.customers.create({
      email,
      name,
    });
  }

  async createSubscription(customerId: string, priceId: string): Promise<Stripe.Subscription> {
    return await this.stripe.subscriptions.create({
      customer: customerId,
      items: [{ price: priceId }],
    });
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Create a Controller to Handle Webhooks

Create a controller to handle incoming webhooks from AppSumo. This controller will use the Stripe service to create a customer and a subscription.

```typescript
import { Controller, Post, Body } from '@nestjs/common';
import { StripeService } from './stripe.service';

@Controller('webhook')
export class WebhookController {
  constructor(private readonly stripeService: StripeService) {}

  @Post()
  async handleWebhook(@Body() body: any): Promise<any> {
    const { email, name } = body;

    // Create a new customer in Stripe
    const customer = await this.stripeService.createCustomer(email, name);

    // Create a new subscription for the customer
    const priceId = 'your_stripe_price_id'; // Replace with your actual price ID
    const subscription = await this.stripeService.createSubscription(customer.id, priceId);

    return { subscriptionId: subscription.id };
  }
}
```

### Step 4: Register the Service and Controller in Your Module

Make sure to register the Stripe service and the Webhook controller in your module.

```typescript
import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';
import { StripeService } from './stripe.service';
import { WebhookController } from './webhook.controller';

@Module({
  providers: [StripeService],
  controllers: [WebhookController],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

### Step 5: Secure Your Webhook Endpoint

Ensure that your webhook endpoint is secure. You can use middleware to verify the webhook signature from AppSumo.

### Example Usage

When AppSumo sends a webhook to your endpoint, the `WebhookController` will handle the request, create a customer in Stripe, and then create a subscription for that customer.

